{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_3cde0b73c7c344aabb0593d7","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# TorchGeo LLM Instructions\n2\t\n3\tDatasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models for geospatial data.\n4\t\n5\t## Commands\n6\t\n7\t```bash\n8\t# Install\n9\tpip install -e \".[all]\"\n10\t\n11\t# Lint (run from repo root)\n12\truff format && ruff check && ty check && prettier --write .\n13\t\n14\t# Test\n15\tpytest --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                        # all (skip slow)\n16\tpytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py                          # single file\n17\tpytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py::TestFooDataset::test_getitem  # single method\n18\tpytest -m \"\" --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                  # include slow\n19\t\n20\t# Docs (requires Pandoc + pip install \".[docs]\")\n21\tcd docs && make clean && make html\n22\t```\n23\t\n24\t## Project Structure\n25\t\n26\t```\n27\ttorchgeo/{datamodules,datasets,losses,models,samplers,trainers,transforms}/\n28\ttests/{data/<dataset>/,datasets/,...}\n29\t```\n30\t\n31\t## Code Style\n32\t\n33\t### File Header (required)\n34\t\n35\t```python\n36\t# Copyright (c) TorchGeo Contributors. All rights reserved.\n37\t# Licensed under the MIT License.\n38\t```\n39\t\n40\t### Formatting (Ruff)\n41\t\n42\t- Single quotes, no trailing commas\n43\t- Imports: isort order (stdlib → third-party → local)\n44\t- Local imports (`from .utils`) in `torchgeo/`; absolute (`from torchgeo`) in `tests/`\n45\t\n46\t### Type Hints (ty)\n47\t\n48\t- All functions require full annotations\n49\t- Union: `X | Y` (not `Union[X, Y]`)\n50\t- Treat `Path` as `type Path = str | os.PathLike[str]` when imported from `torchgeo.datasets.utils`\n51\t- Avoid `Any`; use `Sequence` for parameters, `list`/`tuple` for return values\n52\t- Prefer built-in types (`list`, `dict`, `tuple`) over `typing.List`, etc.\n53\t- `type: ignore` only for external lib issues\n54\t\n55\t### Docstrings (Google style)\n56\t\n57\t```python\n58\tdef func(x: Tensor, weights: Weights | None = None) -> Tensor:\n59\t    \"\"\"Short description.\n60\t\n61\t    Args:\n62\t        x: Input tensor.\n63\t        weights: Pre-trained weights.\n64\t\n65\t    Returns:\n66\t        Output tensor.\n67\t\n68\t    Raises:\n69\t        ValueError: If x is empty.\n70\t\n71\t    Warns:\n72\t        UserWarning: If weights are outdated.\n73\t\n74\t    \"\"\"\n75\t```\n76\t\n77\t- Include `Args`, `Returns`, `Raises`, `Warns` sections as needed\n78\t- Period after first line; blank line after first sentence\n79\t- Don't document default values in Args (Sphinx adds them)\n80\t- `.. versionadded::` for new features; `.. deprecated::` for deprecations\n81\t- Inline comments only for \"why\", not \"what\"\n82\t\n83\t### RST Conventions (docs/docstrings)\n84\t\n85\t- Monospace: double backticks ` ``code`` `\n86\t- Bold: `**text**`\n87\t- Italics: `*text*`\n88\t- Single backticks create links only when followed by underscore; otherwise italics\n89\t- Blank line required before bulleted lists\n90\t\n91\t### Classes\n92\t\n93\t```python\n94\tclass Foo(NonGeoDataset):\n95\t    \"\"\"Dataset description. Citation info.\n96\t\n97\t    .. versionadded:: 0.5\n98\t    \"\"\"\n99\t    url = 'https://...'\n100\t    classes = ['background', 'building']\n101\t\n102\t    def __init__(self, root: Path = 'data', download: bool = False) -> None:\n103\t```\n104\t\n105\t## Testing\n106\t\n107\t```python\n108\tclass TestFooDataset:\n109\t    @pytest.fixture\n110\t    def dataset(self) -> FooDataset:\n111\t        return FooDataset(root='tests/data')\n112\t\n113\t    def test_getitem(self, dataset: FooDataset) -> None:\n114\t        x = dataset[0]\n115\t        assert x['image'].ndim == 3\n116\t        assert x['mask'].ndim == 2\n117\t```\n118\t\n119\t- 100% coverage required; check with `pytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py`\n120\t- Fake data in `tests/data/<dataset>/` (never real data); `data.py` generates it\n121\t- `@pytest.mark.slow` for downloads/network\n122\t- `pytest.importorskip('pkg', minversion='X.X')` for optional deps\n123\t- `plt.close()` at end of plot tests\n124\t\n125\t## Dataset Implementation\n126\t\n127\t```python\n128\tclass MyDataset(RasterDataset):\n129\t    filename_glob = '*.tif'\n130\t    filename_regex = r'^(?P<date>\\d{8})_.*\\.tif$'\n131\t    date_format = '%Y%m%d'\n132\t    is_image = True\n133\t```\n134\t\n135\t- `root='data'` default; `_verify()` for existence checks\n136\t- Sample dict: `{\"image\": tensor, \"mask\": tensor}`\n137\t- PIL for non-geo images, rasterio for geo images\n138\t\n139\t### New Dataset Checklist\n140\t\n141\t1. `torchgeo/datasets/foo.py` (add license header)\n142\t2. Import in `torchgeo/datasets/__init__.py`\n143\t3. `tests/data/foo/data.py` (fake data matching real structure)\n144\t4. `tests/datasets/test_foo.py` (100% coverage)\n145\t5. `docs/api/datasets.rst`\n146\t6. `docs/api/datasets/[non_]geo_datasets.csv`\n147\t\n148\t## Error Handling\n149\t\n150\t- Never catch bare `Exception`; be specific\n151\t- Utilize torchgeo exceptions from `torchgeo.datasets.errors` if applicable, e.g. `DatasetNotFoundError`, `RGBBandsMissingError`, `DependencyNotFoundError`\n152\t- Document in `Raises` section\n153\t- Optional deps: lazy import + helpful ImportError (`'scipy required for ...'`)\n154\t- Use `None` only for mutable defaults; prefer immutable tuples\n155\t\n156\t## Geospatial\n157\t\n158\t- Check \"contains\" not just \"intersects\" for sampling\n159\t- Auto-detect CRS when not specified\n160\t- Warn if datasets have different CRS/res\n161\t- Skip warped bounds computation if CRS matches\n162\t\n163\t## Transforms (Kornia)\n164\t\n165\t- GPU augs in `on_after_batch_transfer`\n166\t- Cast mask to float before Kornia, restore dtype after\n167\t- Masks need channel dim for Kornia, squeeze before loss\n168\t- `AugmentationSequential` requires `data_keys`\n169\t\n170\t## Lightning\n171\t\n172\t- `prepare_data`: downloads only, NO state\n173\t- `setup`: create dataset objects\n174\t- `on_after_batch_transfer`: GPU augmentations\n175\t\n176\t## Performance\n177\t\n178\t- Class attributes for reusable objects (not per-call instantiation)\n179\t- Prefer `einops` operations for readability, like `einops.rearrange` and `einops.reshape`; always specify `dim` in `squeeze()`\n180\t- Checksums slow—make optional\n181\t\n182\t## Models\n183\t\n184\t- Document input/output shapes\n185\t- When modifying conv: update both weight AND `in_channels`\n186\t- `nn.ReLU(inplace=True)` for efficiency\n187\t\n188\t## Dependencies\n189\t\n190\t- Find actual minimum working version; document WHY\n191\t- Sync versions across requirements files\n192\t- Lazy import optional deps inside using function; helpful ImportError message\n193\t\n194\t## Git\n195\t\n196\t- PR titles should match release notes style; use milestones for backports\n197\t- Add license header to new files\n198\t- Update MD5s when test files change\n199\t- Separate logical changes into separate PRs\n200\t- Keep files < 500 LOC\n201\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"958f2dc3-e10d-41c6-8ee9-56e597334e33","uuid":"b8f7f98f-48c2-4ba5-9e3b-86593473ca77","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:59:17.603Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/AGENTS.md","content":"# TorchGeo LLM Instructions\n\nDatasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models for geospatial data.\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\n# Install\npip install -e \".[all]\"\n\n# Lint (run from repo root)\nruff format && ruff check && ty check && prettier --write .\n\n# Test\npytest --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                        # all (skip slow)\npytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py                          # single file\npytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py::TestFooDataset::test_getitem  # single method\npytest -m \"\" --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                  # include slow\n\n# Docs (requires Pandoc + pip install \".[docs]\")\ncd docs && make clean && make html\n```\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\ntorchgeo/{datamodules,datasets,losses,models,samplers,trainers,transforms}/\ntests/{data/<dataset>/,datasets/,...}\n```\n\n## Code Style\n\n### File Header (required)\n\n```python\n# Copyright (c) TorchGeo Contributors. All rights reserved.\n# Licensed under the MIT License.\n```\n\n### Formatting (Ruff)\n\n- Single quotes, no trailing commas\n- Imports: isort order (stdlib → third-party → local)\n- Local imports (`from .utils`) in `torchgeo/`; absolute (`from torchgeo`) in `tests/`\n\n### Type Hints (ty)\n\n- All functions require full annotations\n- Union: `X | Y` (not `Union[X, Y]`)\n- Treat `Path` as `type Path = str | os.PathLike[str]` when imported from `torchgeo.datasets.utils`\n- Avoid `Any`; use `Sequence` for parameters, `list`/`tuple` for return values\n- Prefer built-in types (`list`, `dict`, `tuple`) over `typing.List`, etc.\n- `type: ignore` only for external lib issues\n\n### Docstrings (Google style)\n\n```python\ndef func(x: Tensor, weights: Weights | None = None) -> Tensor:\n    \"\"\"Short description.\n\n    Args:\n        x: Input tensor.\n        weights: Pre-trained weights.\n\n    Returns:\n        Output tensor.\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If x is empty.\n\n    Warns:\n        UserWarning: If weights are outdated.\n\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n- Include `Args`, `Returns`, `Raises`, `Warns` sections as needed\n- Period after first line; blank line after first sentence\n- Don't document default values in Args (Sphinx adds them)\n- `.. versionadded::` for new features; `.. deprecated::` for deprecations\n- Inline comments only for \"why\", not \"what\"\n\n### RST Conventions (docs/docstrings)\n\n- Monospace: double backticks ` ``code`` `\n- Bold: `**text**`\n- Italics: `*text*`\n- Single backticks create links only when followed by underscore; otherwise italics\n- Blank line required before bulleted lists\n\n### Classes\n\n```python\nclass Foo(NonGeoDataset):\n    \"\"\"Dataset description. Citation info.\n\n    .. versionadded:: 0.5\n    \"\"\"\n    url = 'https://...'\n    classes = ['background', 'building']\n\n    def __init__(self, root: Path = 'data', download: bool = False) -> None:\n```\n\n## Testing\n\n```python\nclass TestFooDataset:\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def dataset(self) -> FooDataset:\n        return FooDataset(root='tests/data')\n\n    def test_getitem(self, dataset: FooDataset) -> None:\n        x = dataset[0]\n        assert x['image'].ndim == 3\n        assert x['mask'].ndim == 2\n```\n\n- 100% coverage required; check with `pytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py`\n- Fake data in `tests/data/<dataset>/` (never real data); `data.py` generates it\n- `@pytest.mark.slow` for downloads/network\n- `pytest.importorskip('pkg', minversion='X.X')` for optional deps\n- `plt.close()` at end of plot tests\n\n## Dataset Implementation\n\n```python\nclass MyDataset(RasterDataset):\n    filename_glob = '*.tif'\n    filename_regex = r'^(?P<date>\\d{8})_.*\\.tif$'\n    date_format = '%Y%m%d'\n    is_image = True\n```\n\n- `root='data'` default; `_verify()` for existence checks\n- Sample dict: `{\"image\": tensor, \"mask\": tensor}`\n- PIL for non-geo images, rasterio for geo images\n\n### New Dataset Checklist\n\n1. `torchgeo/datasets/foo.py` (add license header)\n2. Import in `torchgeo/datasets/__init__.py`\n3. `tests/data/foo/data.py` (fake data matching real structure)\n4. `tests/datasets/test_foo.py` (100% coverage)\n5. `docs/api/datasets.rst`\n6. `docs/api/datasets/[non_]geo_datasets.csv`\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- Never catch bare `Exception`; be specific\n- Utilize torchgeo exceptions from `torchgeo.datasets.errors` if applicable, e.g. `DatasetNotFoundError`, `RGBBandsMissingError`, `DependencyNotFoundError`\n- Document in `Raises` section\n- Optional deps: lazy import + helpful ImportError (`'scipy required for ...'`)\n- Use `None` only for mutable defaults; prefer immutable tuples\n\n## Geospatial\n\n- Check \"contains\" not just \"intersects\" for sampling\n- Auto-detect CRS when not specified\n- Warn if datasets have different CRS/res\n- Skip warped bounds computation if CRS matches\n\n## Transforms (Kornia)\n\n- GPU augs in `on_after_batch_transfer`\n- Cast mask to float before Kornia, restore dtype after\n- Masks need channel dim for Kornia, squeeze before loss\n- `AugmentationSequential` requires `data_keys`\n\n## Lightning\n\n- `prepare_data`: downloads only, NO state\n- `setup`: create dataset objects\n- `on_after_batch_transfer`: GPU augmentations\n\n## Performance\n\n- Class attributes for reusable objects (not per-call instantiation)\n- Prefer `einops` operations for readability, like `einops.rearrange` and `einops.reshape`; always specify `dim` in `squeeze()`\n- Checksums slow—make optional\n\n## Models\n\n- Document input/output shapes\n- When modifying conv: update both weight AND `in_channels`\n- `nn.ReLU(inplace=True)` for efficiency\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Find actual minimum working version; document WHY\n- Sync versions across requirements files\n- Lazy import optional deps inside using function; helpful ImportError message\n\n## Git\n\n- PR titles should match release notes style; use milestones for backports\n- Add license header to new files\n- Update MD5s when test files change\n- Separate logical changes into separate PRs\n- Keep files < 500 LOC\n","numLines":201,"startLine":1,"totalLines":201}}}
